centralized seed input so everything will be on the same page (well, seed)
resizing the image to streamline everything and send that same size to each node that asks for how big is it.

the noise is create in this group and then as the node says - injected into the latent.

you can use the prompt if you want help the generation of the noise but in most cases i found it to be unnecessary.
this is the image that will be injected to the latent, the stronger you set it, the lower this is - the more freedom the model will have during generation

I like to save all steps, feel free to turn off which part you like or completely delete it.

since i like to show off my images on social media, i like them to be orgnized verticly, you can choose any other way with the image concatenate node above this part.
SVD is straight forward - you can play with the motion bucket ID to get different camera movements, but try not to touch the rest if you don't know what you're doing.

using less than 15-20 steps will resolve pretty much the same image and not a big change.
I found that on most images, the magic area  ~30 steps and 4 cfg - but YMMV
